  "prompt": "How do you deposit cash at an ATM?",
  "response": "Depositing cash at an ATM is a convenient way to add funds to your bank account. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you through the process:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Deposit Cash at an ATM:**\n\n1. **Locate a Compatible ATM**  \n   - Ensure the ATM is affiliated with your bank or supports cash deposits. Most ATMs display deposit capabilities on the screen or signage.\n\n2. **Insert Your Debit Card**  \n   - Insert your debit card into the ATM and follow the prompts to enter your PIN.\n\n3. **Select \"Deposit\"**  \n   - From the main menu, choose the \u201cDeposit\u201d option.\n\n4. **Choose the Account Type**  \n   - Select the account where you want to deposit the cash (e.g., checking or savings).\n\n5. **Insert Cash**  \n   - If the ATM has a cash slot or deposit envelope, follow the on-screen instructions:\n     - Some ATMs require you to place the cash directly into the slot.\n     - Others may require you to insert the cash into a provided envelope (be sure to fill out the envelope if required).\n\n6. **Confirm the Amount**  \n   - The ATM will display the total amount of cash deposited. Verify that it matches what you intended to deposit.\n\n7. **Complete the Transaction**  \n   - Confirm the deposit and take your receipt if offered.\n\n8. **Remove Your Card**  \n   - Don\u2019t forget to take your debit card and any cash or receipt before leaving.\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Depositing Cash at an ATM:**\n- **Check limits:** Some ATMs have daily deposit limits.\n- **Use your bank\u2019s ATM:** Your own bank\u2019s ATM may process deposits faster than a third-party ATM.\n- **Count your cash beforehand:** Ensure the amount you\u2019re depositing is accurate before inserting it into the ATM.\n- **Keep your receipt:** Save your receipt as proof of the transaction until the deposit is reflected in your account.\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure about the process, consult your bank\u2019s instructions or contact customer service for assistance.",
